This paper deals with wireless network architecture and resource allocation, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses traffic shaping games and optimization, which could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses the issue of network dimensioning, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulations of a wireless infrastructure, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
